  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Evaluate the efficacy of a multimodal hand hygiene system in the intensive care unit
      environment and evaluate any impact on health care associated infections.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Deploy and utilize a novel body worn hand hygiene system that incorporates provider and group
      specific feedback allowing hand hygiene to occur directly within the patient environment. We
      hypothesize that by improving provider hand hygiene we will reduce health-care associated
      infection rates.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
